## Vercel Web Analytics Installation - Complete

Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for this vanilla HTML project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

### What was implemented:

**Framework Identified:** Vanilla HTML/JavaScript
- This is a static HTML site with no framework (not Next.js, React, Vue, etc.)

**Package Installation:**
- The `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already present in package.json
- Ran `pnpm install` to ensure dependencies are properly installed

**Analytics Configuration:**
Updated both HTML files to use the CDN-based Web Analytics script:

**Modified Files:**
1. `src/index.html` - Updated Web Analytics script tag
2. `src/privacy.html` - Updated Web Analytics script tag

**Changes Made:**
- Changed script source from `/_vercel/insights/script.js` (old path) to `https://cdn.vercel-insights.com/v1/script.js` (official CDN)
- This is the recommended approach for vanilla HTML projects according to Vercel's official documentation
- The script loads asynchronously with `defer` attribute for optimal performance

**Implementation Details:**
According to the official Vercel documentation, for vanilla HTML projects, the recommended approach is to use the CDN script tag:
```html
<script defer src="https://cdn.vercel-insights.com/v1/script.js"></script>
```

This approach:
- Works immediately without additional configuration
- Automatically tracks page views
- Loads asynchronously to avoid blocking page rendering
- Uses the official Vercel CDN for optimal delivery

**Verification:**
- Confirmed both HTML files now include the correct Web Analytics script
- No build process required for this vanilla HTML project
- Analytics will start tracking once deployed to Vercel

**Next Steps:**
After deployment, you can:
1. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section
2. Verify tracking is working by checking the Network tab for requests to the analytics endpoint
3. Wait a few days for meaningful traffic data to accumulate

**Note:** The previous implementation was using `/_vercel/insights/script.js` which is the path for Vercel Speed Insights (performance monitoring). The new implementation uses the correct Web Analytics script for visitor and page view tracking.
